      "source": [
        "# PinholeCamera"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A `PinholeCamera` represents the classic pinhole camera model, which is fundamental in 3D computer vision. It describes how 3D points in the world are projected onto a 2D image plane.\n",
        "\n",
        "The `PinholeCamera` in GTSAM is a templated class, `PinholeCamera<CALIBRATION>`, meaning it can work with various intrinsic calibration models. A common instantiation is `gtsam.PinholeCameraCal3_S2`, which uses `gtsam.Cal3_S2` for its intrinsic parameters. This guide will use `PinholeCameraCal3_S2` for examples.\n",
        "\n",
        "A `PinholeCamera` combines two key components:\n",
        "1.  **Extrinsic Parameters**: The camera's 3D pose (position and orientation) in the world, represented by a `gtsam.Pose3` object.\n",
        "2.  **Intrinsic Parameters**: The internal optical characteristics of the camera, represented by a `CALIBRATION` object (e.g., `gtsam.Cal3_S2`), which includes parameters like focal length, principal point, and skew."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "<a href=\"https://colab.research.google.com/github/borglab/gtsam/blob/develop/gtsam/geometry/doc/PinholeCamera.ipynb\" target=\"_parent\"><img src=\"https://colab.research.google.com/assets/colab-badge.svg\" alt=\"Open In Colab\"/></a>"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 1,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Note: you may need to restart the kernel to use updated packages.\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "%pip install --quiet gtsam-develop"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 2,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import gtsam\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from gtsam import Cal3_S2, Pose3, Point3, Point2, Rot3\n",
        "# PinholeCamera is a template, PinholeCameraCal3_S2 is a common typedef\n",
        "from gtsam import PinholeCameraCal3_S2"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Initialization\n",
        "\n",
        "A `PinholeCameraCal3_S2` can be initialized by providing its pose and intrinsic calibration."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 3,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Default Camera (cam0):\n"
          ]
        },
        {
          "ename": "AttributeError",
          "evalue": "'gtsam.gtsam.PinholeCameraCal3_S2' object has no attribute 'print_'",
          "output_type": "error",
          "traceback": [
            "\u001b[31m---------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[39m",
            "\u001b[31mAttributeError\u001b[39m                            Traceback (most recent call last)",
            "\u001b[36mCell\u001b[39m\u001b[36m \u001b[39m\u001b[32mIn[3]\u001b[39m\u001b[32m, line 4\u001b[39m\n\u001b[32m      2\u001b[39m cam0 = PinholeCameraCal3_S2()\n\u001b[32m      3\u001b[39m \u001b[38;5;28mprint\u001b[39m(\u001b[33m\"\u001b[39m\u001b[33mDefault Camera (cam0):\u001b[39m\u001b[33m\"\u001b[39m)\n\u001b[32m----> \u001b[39m\u001b[32m4\u001b[39m \u001b[43mcam0\u001b[49m\u001b[43m.\u001b[49m\u001b[43mprint_\u001b[49m(\u001b[33m\"\u001b[39m\u001b[33mcam0\u001b[39m\u001b[33m\"\u001b[39m) \u001b[38;5;66;03m# This will print both pose and calibration\u001b[39;00m\n\u001b[32m      5\u001b[39m \u001b[38;5;28mprint\u001b[39m(\u001b[33m\"\u001b[39m\u001b[33m\"\u001b[39m)\n\u001b[32m      7\u001b[39m \u001b[38;5;66;03m# 2. Constructor with Pose3 and Cal3_S2\u001b[39;00m\n",
            "\u001b[31mAttributeError\u001b[39m: 'gtsam.gtsam.PinholeCameraCal3_S2' object has no attribute 'print_'"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# 1. Default constructor: Identity pose, default Cal3_S2 calibration\n",
        "cam0 = PinholeCameraCal3_S2()\n",
        "print(\"Default Camera (cam0):\")\n",
        "cam0.print_(\"cam0\") # This will print both pose and calibration\n",
        "print(\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Constructor with Pose3 and Cal3_S2\n",
        "camera_pose = Pose3(Rot3.Ypr(-np.pi/2, 0, -np.pi/2), Point3(1, 0, 0.5))\n",
        "K_intrinsics = Cal3_S2(150.0, 150.0, 0.0, 320.0, 240.0)\n",
        "cam1 = PinholeCameraCal3_S2(camera_pose, K_intrinsics)\n",
        "print(\"Custom Camera (cam1):\")\n",
        "cam1.print_(\"cam1\")\n",
        "print(\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Using the static lookAt method\n",
        "eye = Point3(0, 0, 10)      # Camera position in world\n",
        "target = Point3(0, 0, 0)    # Point the camera is looking at\n",
        "upVector = Point3(0, 1, 0)  # Defines the 'up' direction of the camera in the world (world's Y-axis)\n",
        "K_lookat = Cal3_S2(100.0, 100.0, 0.0, 50.0, 50.0)\n",
        "cam_lookat = PinholeCameraCal3_S2.lookAt(eye, target, upVector, K_lookat)\n",
        "print(\"LookAt Camera (cam_lookat):\")\n",
        "cam_lookat.print_(\"cam_lookat\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Accessing Parameters\n",
        "\n",
        "The extrinsic pose and intrinsic calibration can be easily accessed:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "cam1_pose = cam1.pose()\n",
        "cam1_K = cam1.calibration()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Cam1 Pose:\")\n",
        "cam1_pose.print_(\"\") # Pose3 has its own print method\n",
        "print(\"\\nCam1 Calibration (K):\")\n",
        "cam1_K.print_(\"\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Core Operations: Projection and Back-Projection"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### `project(point_C)`\n",
        "The `project(point_C)` method takes a `gtsam.Point3` specified in the **camera coordinate frame** ($P_c$) and projects it onto the 2D image plane, returning a `gtsam.Point2` in pixel coordinates.\n",
        "It will throw a `CheiralityException` if the point is behind the camera ($Z_c \\le 0$)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "P_camera_frame = Point3(1.0, 0.5, 5.0) # A 3D point in front of the camera, in camera's own frame\n",
        "print(f\"3D point in Camera Frame (P_c): {P_camera_frame}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "p_pixel_projected = cam1.project(P_camera_frame)\n",
        "print(f\"Projected 2D point (p_pixel): {p_pixel_projected}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Jacobians for project(P_camera_frame)\n",
        "Dpose = np.zeros((2, 6), order='F')      # Derivative wrt 6 Pose3 parameters\n",
        "Dpoint = np.zeros((2, 3), order='F')     # Derivative wrt 3 Point3 parameters\n",
        "Dcal = np.zeros((2, 5), order='F')       # Derivative wrt 5 Cal3_S2 parameters\n",
        "projected_point_again = cam1.project(P_camera_frame, Dpose, Dpoint, Dcal)\n",
        "print(f\"\\nJacobians for project(P_c):\")\n",
        "print(f\"Dpose (dP_pixel / dPose):\\n{Dpose}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Dpoint (dP_pixel / dP_camera):\\n{Dpoint}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Dcal (dP_pixel / dCal):\\n{Dcal}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Example of CheiralityException\n",
        "P_behind = Point3(1.0, 0.5, -5.0) # Point behind the camera (negative Z in camera frame)\n",
        "print(f\"\\nProjecting point behind camera: {P_behind}\")\n",
        "try:\n",
        "    cam1.project(P_behind)\n",
        "except gtsam.CheiralityException as e:\n",
        "    print(f\"\\nCaught expected CheiralityException: {e}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### `projectSafe(point_C)`\n",
        "The `projectSafe(point_C)` method is a safer alternative that checks for cheirality. It returns a pair: the projected `Point2` and a boolean flag indicating if the projection was valid (i.e., point was in front of the camera)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "print(\"Projecting P_camera_frame with projectSafe:\")\n",
        "projected_safe, valid_safe = cam1.projectSafe(P_camera_frame)\n",
        "print(f\"  Projected point: {projected_safe}\")\n",
        "print(f\"  Is valid? {valid_safe}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "P_behind_camera_frame = Point3(1.0, 0.5, -2.0) # Another point behind the camera\n",
        "print(\"\\nProjecting P_behind_camera_frame with projectSafe:\")\n",
        "projected_behind_safe, valid_behind_safe = cam1.projectSafe(P_behind_camera_frame)\n",
        "print(f\"  Projected point: {projected_behind_safe} (may be non-physical if invalid)\")\n",
        "print(f\"  Is valid? {valid_behind_safe}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### `backproject(p_pixel, depth)`\n",
        "The `backproject(p_pixel, depth)` method takes a 2D point `p_pixel` in pixel coordinates and a `depth` (distance from the camera center along the $Z_c$ axis) and returns the corresponding 3D point in the **camera coordinate frame**."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "p_pixel_to_backproject = Point2(350.0, 255.0) \n",
        "depth_val = 5.0\n",
        "print(f\"Pixel point p_pixel: {p_pixel_to_backproject}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Depth: {depth_val}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "P_c_recovered = cam1.backproject(p_pixel_to_backproject, depth_val)\n",
        "print(f\"Back-projected 3D point (P_c_recovered): {P_c_recovered}\")\n",
        "# This should be equal to P_camera_frame = Point3(1.0, 0.5, 5.0) used in project() example"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Manifold Operations\n",
        "\n",
        "`PinholeCamera` is a manifold. Its dimension is the sum of the dimensions of its `Pose3` component (6) and its `CALIBRATION` component (e.g., 5 for `Cal3_S2`), totaling 11 for `PinholeCameraCal3_S2`."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "print(\"Original cam1:\")\n",
        "cam1.print_(\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Delta vector: first 6 for Pose3, next 5 for Cal3_S2\n",
        "delta_pose = np.array([0.01, 0.02, 0.03, 0.1, 0.2, 0.3]) # dtranslation, drotation_vector\n",
        "delta_cal = np.array([10.0, -5.0, 0.01, 1.0, 2.0])      # dfx,dfy,ds,du0,dv0\n",
        "delta_combined = np.concatenate((delta_pose, delta_cal))\n",
        "print(f\"\\nDelta vector (dim={len(delta_combined)}): {delta_combined}\\n\")\n",
        "\n",
        "cam_retracted = cam1.retract(delta_combined)\n",
        "print(\"Retracted cam_retracted:\")\n",
        "cam_retracted.print_(\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "local_coords = cam1.localCoordinates(cam_retracted)\n",
        "print(\"\\nLocal coordinates from cam1 to cam_retracted:\")\n",
        "print(local_coords) # Should be very close to delta_combined"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Utility Functions"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "print(\"cam1:\")\n",
        "cam1.print_(\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "cam1_copy = PinholeCameraCal3_S2(cam1.pose(), cam1.calibration())\n",
        "print(\"\\ncam1_copy (from pose and K of cam1):\")\n",
        "cam1_copy.print_(\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\ncam1 equals cam1_copy? {cam1.equals(cam1_copy, 1e-9)}\")\n",
        "print(f\"cam1 equals cam0 (default camera)? {cam1.equals(cam0, 1e-9)}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
